{
  "topicId": "logic-gates-boolean-algebra",
  "mcqs": [
    {
      "id": "mcq-1",
      "question": "The output of a 2-input NAND gate is 0 when:",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "Both inputs are 0"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "Both inputs are 1"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "Any one input is 1"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "Any one input is 0"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "B",
      "explanation": "NAND gate produces 0 only when ALL inputs are 1. For all other input combinations, output is 1.",
      "difficulty": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-2",
      "question": "Which logic gate is known as the universal gate?",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "AND gate"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "OR gate"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "NAND gate"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "NOT gate"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "C",
      "explanation": "NAND gate is called a universal gate because any boolean function can be implemented using only NAND gates.",
      "difficulty": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-3",
      "question": "The Boolean expression Y = A + B represents:",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "AND operation"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "OR operation"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "NOT operation"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "NAND operation"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "B",
      "explanation": "In Boolean algebra, the + symbol represents OR (addition) operation, while \u00b7 or concatenation represents AND operation.",
      "difficulty": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-4",
      "question": "Which gate produces output 1 for odd number of 1s in inputs?",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "XOR gate"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "XNOR gate"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "AND gate"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "OR gate"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "A",
      "explanation": "XOR (Exclusive OR) gate outputs 1 when there is an odd number of 1s in the input, i.e., when inputs are different.",
      "difficulty": "medium"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-5",
      "question": "According to De Morgan's theorem, (A\u00b7B)' is equal to:",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "A' + B'"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "A' \u00b7 B'"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "A + B"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "A'B + AB'"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "A",
      "explanation": "De Morgan's First Theorem states: (A\u00b7B)' = A' + B'. The complement of a product equals the sum of complements.",
      "difficulty": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-6",
      "question": "The dual of A + 1 = 1 is:",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "A \u00b7 0 = 0"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "A \u00b7 1 = A"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "A + 0 = A"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "A \u00b7 A = A"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "A",
      "explanation": "The dual of a boolean expression is obtained by swapping AND with OR and 0 with 1. So A + 1 = 1 becomes A \u00b7 0 = 0.",
      "difficulty": "medium"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-7",
      "question": "Which law states that A + (B\u00b7C) = (A + B)\u00b7(A + C)?",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "Associative Law"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "Distributive Law"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "Commutative Law"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "Absorption Law"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "B",
      "explanation": "The second distributive law states: A + (B\u00b7C) = (A + B)\u00b7(A + C). This is the dual of the first distributive law.",
      "difficulty": "medium"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-8",
      "question": "A 3-input AND gate produces output 1 when:",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "At least one input is 1"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "At least two inputs are 1"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "All three inputs are 1"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "All inputs are 0"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "C",
      "explanation": "AND gate produces 1 only when ALL inputs are 1, regardless of the number of inputs.",
      "difficulty": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-9",
      "question": "The complement of variable A is represented as:",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
